resource.name: Individual-Report-Scenario
resource.description: A Receiver uses $evaluate-measure to request the data and results for an Individual measure from a Reporter.  The Receiver receives a completed MeasureReport and verifies that it has the correct data and the calculated result is correct for the individual.  The request is for json format as a default.  Prequisite: appropriate measures data is loaded to the server under test.

test.name: Eval-Measure-Query
test.description: Query using $evaluate-measure, including a measure, subject, and period start and end dates. Expected response is a MeasureReport with a denom count of 1.

assert.description: Confirm that the request HTTP Header Accept contains 'charset=utf-8'.
Confirm that the request HTTP Header Content-Type contains 'charset=utf-8'.
Confirm that the returned HTTP status is 200(OK).
Confirm that the response HTTP Header Content-Type contains 'charset=utf-8'.
Confirm that the response body contains a MeasureReport resource
Validate the response MeasureReport for conformance.
Verify that the Measure Score is as expected in the response
Verify that the Initial Population Count is as expected in the response
Verify that the Denominator Count is as expected in the response
When using a MeasureReport resource to represent the results of an individual calculation, the MeasureReport SHALL have a reference to the subject of the report
When using a MeasureReport resource to represent the results of an individual calculation, the MeasureReport SHALL have a type-code of 'individual'
